 \subsection{Extension to the $t$-score}
 In most standard statistical procedures and texts, the researcher is directed
 to use the t-statistic when the sample size is insufficiently large for the
 z-score. The $t$-statistic is given by $t = \frac{x-\bar{x}}{s/\sqrt{n}} =
 \sqrt{n}z$, since $\sigma$ is replaced by $s$ in the $z-$score when used for
 large samples. Thus the following corollary is immediate:

